messages.text: Cal? Are you there?
Can we talk?
I don‚Äôt know if talking is a good idea.
Please. Just a few minutes.
I‚Äôm home already.
Then I‚Äôll come over.
I dunno.
Please? I won‚Äôt be long. Dad told me you broke up with Selena.
We weren‚Äôt ever really dating, but yeah, I told her we shouldn‚Äôt see each other anymore.
Why?
I think you know why.
Tell me anyway.
You‚Äôve got my head spinning.
If I come over, I‚Äôll do more than that.
Somehow, I don‚Äôt think that would help. It would be awesome‚Ä¶
But it wouldn‚Äôt make our decision clearer.
Cal‚Ä¶I still love you.
A few minutes pass.
Cal?
I‚Äôm sorry, Jenn. I just‚Ä¶can‚Äôt.
Three weeks pass.
Hi, hon. How are you?
I‚Äôm okay.
You know I can tell when you‚Äôre lying.
Well, I‚Äôm still thinking about Cal. His birthday‚Äôs on Friday.
Wish him a happy birthday!
It‚Äôs not so simple. He doesn‚Äôt want me, and yet I think he was the one.
You know the only true ‚Äòone‚Äô for yourself is you.
I know. That‚Äôs why I made some serious changes. I got a new job, remember?
How was the first day?
Awesome, actually. Finally doing what I love‚Äî
Might not be making a ton, but at least I have my foot in the door at the record label.
I‚Äôm proud of you for that. Did you tell Cal?
What would it matter?
He doesn‚Äôt feel the same way about me as I do about him.
He loves you.
Loved, Dad. Past tense.
You so sure about that?
Has he told you something?
A dad just knows these things. #DadThing #DadIntiution #DadKnows
Seriously, Dad. The hashtags!!
Would you rather I just say I‚Äôm awesome and I know everything? Without the #?
The # makes it seem less like bragging.
You mean more like bragging.
Call Cal.
What if he doesn‚Äôt want to talk to me?
He‚Äôll always want to talk to you. Don‚Äôt you know he‚Äôs crazy about you and always will be?
Why else do you think he took that job in San Francisco?
Because they‚Äôre paying him a ton?
Because he didn‚Äôt get other offers?
Nope. After he finished his residency, he had offers in New York, Chicago AND San Francisco‚Äî
He‚Äôs an amazing surgeon, you know?
But he took the job that would take him to your city. It wasn‚Äôt even the best paying job!
Seriously? Then why didn‚Äôt he call me when he got here?
He wasn‚Äôt sure about how you‚Äôd react. I think he was hoping to run into you.
And then Spark intervened! It was fate.
Do you think?
#ForSure #Truth #CallTheBoyAlready
On Friday, Jenn works up the courage to text Cal.
Just wanted to wish you a happy birthday.
Thanks.
Also‚Ä¶just wanted to tell you that you were right.
About what?
I DO like bright and shiny things‚Ä¶
And I WAS unhappy and looking to you to rescue me.
I see.
That‚Äôs why I decided to rescue myself. I got a new job.
Really?
Yeah. I‚Äôm an assistant at Rebel Records. I‚Äôm not doing music yet, but at least I‚Äôve got my foot in the door.
That‚Äôs awesome, Jenn ‚Äî congrats!!
Thanks. I‚Äôm hardly making anything, but at least now I‚Äôm closer to doing what I love.
My boss listened to a couple of my tracks yesterday. He might even use one.
I‚Äôm so happy for you! That‚Äôs great!!
By the way, I got something. For you. For your birthday.
You didn‚Äôt have to do that!
Can I bring it over?
OK
Two hours later, Jenn stands at Cal‚Äôs front door.
She rings the doorbell and Cal swings open the door.
He looks as handsome as ever in his button-down shirt and khakis.
Jenn feels her throat constrict.
Hey.
Hey.
Jenn stands awkwardly on the porch.
Want to come in?
Jenn nods a little too eagerly.
She hands him a small, wrapped gift.
Tentatively, he opens it.
Inside, is an old mini iPod.
Where did you get this?
Facebook Marketplace. Couldn‚Äôt find a blue one like you had, so I got silver.
I put all your favorite songs on it, but maybe we can add new ones too‚Ä¶
Cal stares at the old iPod for a long time.
You didn‚Äôt have to do this.
I know. But I was sorry I made you give up your old one.
I shouldn‚Äôt have even cared about how you listened to your music. I should‚Äôve let you be yourself.
You‚Äôre amazing, Cal, just as you are.
And you were right that I kept trying to change you‚Äî
When I really just wanted to change myself.
Did you? Change what you wanted to change?
Yeah, I think so.
Cal pulls Jenn in for hug.
She wraps his arms around him.
I‚Äôm so sorry I messed everything up.
Tears spring to Jenn‚Äôs eyes.
I should‚Äôve told you then how I felt‚Äî
About the iPod, about everything. It‚Äôs my fault, too.
I was in a slump when we were together. And without even knowing it‚Ä¶
You helped me get out of it. We should have done that together in the first place.
Cal strokes Jenn‚Äôs hair, and then Jenn pulls back to look into his eyes.
I know. Because it‚Äôs just‚Ä¶
I‚Äôve got the perfect job now, and I should be happy‚Ä¶
But I miss you, Cal. I‚Ä¶
I still love you.
Cal freezes, staring at Jenn.
You do?
Yes, I do.
Thank God. Because I love you, too.
Cal dips down to kiss Jenn.
Their lips meet and instantly, the kiss turns passionate.
Jenn breaks for a breath.
Are you sure about this?
What about Selena? All the other women on Spark?
I‚Äôve always loved you, Jenn. You‚Äôve always been the woman for me‚Äî
I‚Äôve never wanted anybody else.
Good. Because I promise never to take you for granted ever again.
Same here ‚Äî I‚Äôm going to be thankful for every day I‚Äôm with you, Jenn.
You‚Äôre the most amazing woman I‚Äôve ever met.
And you‚Äôre the most amazing man.
So‚Ä¶should we call your dad? He‚Äôll want to get his wedding binder out.
Nah. Let‚Äôs let him sweat it out a bit longer.
Jenn throws her arms around Cal‚Äôs neck.
And they kiss ‚Äî for what feels like forever.
